WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.532
Certification for Dental Assistants


00:00:02.532 --> 00:00:04.579
DANB Certification:


00:00:04.579 --> 00:00:12.312
Achieving DANB (Dental Assisting National Board) certifications, such as CDA, COA, and NELDA, enhances


00:00:12.312 --> 00:00:16.928
a dental assistant's professional credibility and demonstrates a commitment to high standards in patient


00:00:16.928 --> 00:00:17.710
care.


00:00:17.710 --> 00:00:21.298
These certifications can lead to increased earning potential and greater career


00:00:21.298 --> 00:00:25.410
advancement, as many employers prefer certified candidates for their skills and


00:00:25.410 --> 00:00:26.582
knowledge.


00:00:26.582 --> 00:00:28.799
Pathways to Certification:


00:00:28.799 --> 00:00:31.556
Graduation from Accredited Programs:


00:00:31.556 --> 00:00:37.736
Completing a CODA-accredited dental assisting program provides the necessary education and clinical experience.


00:00:37.736 --> 00:00:39.402
Work Experience:


00:00:39.402 --> 00:00:45.179
Significant hands-on experience in a dental setting can also qualify candidates for certification.


00:00:45.179 --> 00:00:47.085
Prior Certifications:


00:00:47.085 --> 00:00:52.230
Existing relevant certifications may allow for an expedited certification process.


00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:57.570
By pursuing these pathways, dental assistants can enhance their careers in a growing profession.

